snippet.textDisplay:
There has never been peace without first a great suffering, the greater the suffering, the greater the peace. As mankind is drawn to his self-destruction like a moth to the candle, the so-called defenders of peace – the church, the government, the law – work tirelessly to save humanity from itself. But, by averting disaster, they serve to delay a peace that can only come through an inevitable baptism of fire.
The coronavirus is not the beginning of the end. It is the beginning of a greater mutual understanding through common suffering. It is the first step towards the ultimate brotherhood of man. The suffering is the bridge to ultimate peace.

Today, mankind has been handed the opportunity to escape his destiny, an otherwise inevitable conclusion to a thousand years of intolerance and fear.

I call all rationalists who can stand and join in the struggle against the radical theists, all of which fall beneath a common umbrella of ideology. If we were to continue any further we would reach mythology and Aesop’s fables. When do we stop?

Any belief in a spirituality with no other proof, other than the cravings to project one’s self over the rational thinking of the others must be eradicated as it does not only halt progression and development of the human mind and reach, but also hinders it.

Here I will emphasize clearly that the judgment upheld against us will be one of human hands, not of a god or other worldly being. Part of the absurd rational is what leads to the obscure justifications, the believers place upon their own disgraceful and belligerent behavior.

No. The loss of human life cannot and will not be justified. For this is not the taking of human lives. They are merely puppets, hollow shells that were once human beings. Brainwashed by stories and tales of old, their weak minds have been overpowered by the pressure placed on them by other lifeless puppets. And so, the cycle continues.

On February 29, there were 100 infected in France, 77 in Germany and only 45 in the Spanish state, less than half that in France. But the lousy management of the Spanish government, made it ignore the request of the Catalan Generalitat to decree confinement, instead of which Pedro Sánchez preferred to STEAL the Health powers already transferred from years before to the Generalitat, and put the "efficient" ;-) Spanish army in the midst of this very complicated health situation

As of today, March 28, 2020, those infected in the Spanish state exceed 65,000, and the dead are more than 5,000, with Spain being the 3rd country in the world (after China and Italy) in morbidity and mortality.

Dr. Haseltine's referenced hydroxychloroquine study has incredibly poor sample bias: 1. sample size was 30 but only 1 severe patient; 2. of the 15 subject placebo group, they got better naturally in 1-9 days; 3. of the test group, got better in 1-4 days. why would you choose a sample where at least half the cases were already 1-to-4.5 days away from not just full recovery of symptoms, but 1-to-4.5 days away from testing NEGATIVE -- which can naturally take up to 10 days after symptoms disappear.by any conservative measure, 'most' of the sample was 75%-to-95% already recovered not just from symptoms but actually testing negative.

test it again with 50+ cases that are at least 1 week away from being symptom free -- NOT from outright being negative.

and then test it again with 50+ SEVERE cases

i'm still not sure how effective it is, if at all.

but that test is clearly deeply flawed and someone like Dr. Haseltine should know better.

snippet.textDisplay:
new study disputing hydroxychloroquine is deeply flawed. First, only 1 severe patient.The other 29 were not severe and could have been getting better regardless. Also, the 15 who took it got better in 1-4 days. Others got better in 1-9 days. 'Ineffective' on ppl who naturally recovered in 1-3 days proves nothing. Why would you pick 29 of 30 patients who were not severe, but also already 70-95% recovered?

Should be testing on ppl who are at least 7-10 days away from recovery, and especially severe cases.

And irregardless, those that took the drug got better up to 2x as fast. 4 days vs 9 is still promising.

But clearly this test had terrible sample bias. It's not even remotely reflective of an average sample of cases.

It should be people who are at least 1-1.5 weeks away from natural recovery and be tested on at least 10-15% severe cases -- or better yet, specifically on severe cases.

This man is clearly very well educated and I have to assume he did not fully read that particular study yet as any scholar would note how flawed that sample selection was.
